com.example.cardiobook

Class AddBP

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.cardiobook.BPs
      • com.example.cardiobook.AddBP
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AddBP
extends BPs

    AddBP is used to add a new blood pressure entry by using the abstract data type BPs. It can either be called with a comment or without a comment.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    kyle

        public AddBP(java.lang.String day,

      throws InvalidInt

        AddBP is used to add a new blood pressure entry by using the abstract data type BPs. This will make a new BP without a comment.

        Parameters:
        day - date of the new BP to be entered
        time - time of the new BP to be entered
        systolic - systolic pressure of the new BP to be entered
        diastolic - diastolic pressure of the new BP to be entered
        rate - heart rate of the new BP to be entered
        position - position of the new BP to be entered
        Throws:
        InvalidInt - exception called when entry is invalid
